## How the Five Pages Connect

The five moments form a closed loop that feeds itself:

**Sprint Launch** establishes the intent and creates the team alignment artifact. Its executive summary and sprint theme become the opening frame of the entire quarter.

**Status Tracker** collects the operational ground truth throughout the quarter. Every status update, every blocked flag, every note is raw input for everything that follows.

**Momentum Synthesis** translates that ground truth into strategic meaning on demand. It keeps the founder oriented without requiring them to analyze data themselves.

**Sprint Wind-Down** creates intentional closure and begins seeding the next cycle. The decisions made here feed the retrospective and pre-populate the next Quarter Map.

**Retrospective** closes the loop and opens the next one. Its Forward Guidance becomes the starting context for the next sprint's planning — so the platform learns with the founder quarter over quarter.

A founder who completes all five moments at the end of a year has not just run four quarters. They have built a documented record of their agency's strategic development — a year-over-year account of what they prioritized, what they built, and how their capabilities evolved. That record is uniquely valuable and not replicable outside this platform.

That is what earns Architect OS its place.

